ode at (3.9,4.25) {20'};\draw (4.1,3.8) -- (4.2,3.8);\draw (4.1,4) -- (4.2,4);\draw (4.15,3.8) -- (4.15,4);
ode at (4.25,3.9) {20'};
ode at (2,3.8) {400'};
ode at (3.8,2) {400'};\end{tikzpicture}Sarah runs around the block on the $400$-foot side of the street, while Sam runs on the opposite side of the street. How many more feet than Sarah does Sam run for every lap around the block?
